<h1>Electrical interface for the SpectraLight 0200 Controller</h1><p>&nbsp;</p><p> This page documents the 25 pin connector on the SpectraLight 0200 controller box.  </p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img src="/site/meshcms/generated/spectralight0200protocol/DB25pinout.jpg/org.meshcms.core.ResizedThumbnail/resized-8598026.jpg" alt="" width="386" height="189" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p><table border="0"><tbody><tr><td> Pin</td><td>Function <br /></td><td> Notes</td></tr><tr><td> 1</td><td>Accessory Input <br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 2</td><td> Clamp Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 3 </td><td> ??? (+5v)<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 4</td><td> Spindle Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 5</td><td> Z Dir Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 6</td><td> X Dir Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 7</td><td> GND</td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 8</td><td> Y Dir Change Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 9</td><td> Z High Speed Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 10</td><td> ??? (0v)<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 11</td><td> Cover Open Output<br /></td><td>+5v when cover is open <br /></td></tr><tr><td> 12</td><td> ??? (0v)<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 13</td><td> ??? (+5v)<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 14</td><td> X Dir Change Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 15</td><td> Robot 1 Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 16</td><td> Robot 2 Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 17</td><td> Mill Enable Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 18</td><td> Y Dir Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 19</td><td> Z Step Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 20</td><td> X Step Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 21</td><td> Y Step Input<br /></td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> 22</td><td> Manual Mode Output<br /></td><td> +5v when the spidle is set to manual speed control.  Otherwise this pin functions as spindle enable input. </td></tr><tr><td> 23</td><td> EStop / 25µs clock<br /></td><td> +5v Carrier with a pulse every 25µs, 0v with no pulse when the estop button is pressed<br /></td></tr><tr><td> 24</td><td> Limit Switch / 25µs clock<br /></td><td>  +5v Carrier with a pulse every 25µs, 0v with no pulse when thelimit switch is activated<br /></td></tr><tr><td> 25</td><td> ??? (0v)</td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Note, your controller should look like the photo below from the back.  If it doesn't, this cable will not work.</p><img src="lmc_controller.jpg" alt="" /><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>
 
    
